review_blob: Draft at Good Karma 12/16/15. Pours a hazy golden orange color with a thin white head. Aroma is huge fruit: apricot, peach, melon, subtle berries. Mouthful is medium consistent with an unfiltered wheat beer with moderate carbonation. Flavor is well balanced sweet and tart, malty, wheat, apricot, peach, subtle melon and salt mid palate and a tangy finish. Probably the best balanced fruited beer I've had. Definitely delivers on apricot flavor better than any other!

Poured into a snifter from bottle. Pours dark brown with minimal white head and modest lacing. Aroma is heavy vanilla and bourbon. Mouthfeel is medium to full-bodied. Taste is dominated by vanilla. A good beer, but not as good as the original or iced versions.

Draft @ Ale Arsenal. Pours a golden yellow with nice white head and some lacing. Early pours were more hazy, but this beer has self-clarified with time. Aroma is piney with lots of citrus and tropical fruits and sweet malt. Mouthfeel is medium to full bodied for an IPA. Taste is a great mix of malt, bread, tropical fruit, pine, and citrus. Alcohol is well hidden in this 12.5% beast of a triple IPA. Definitely my favorite AA IPA so far and a fitting tribute to Randy.

Bottle @ CBS on 4/14/15. Pours black with minimal tan head that dissipates quickly. Aroma of chocolate, vanilla, molasses, roasted malt and bourbon. Medium mouthfeel. Taste of bourbon, molasses, roasted malt, chocolate with some hints of oak and vanilla. Definitely one of the best Eclipses. Tough to tell if its declined a little with age, as others have suggested.
beer_name: FiftyFifty Imperial Eclipse Stout - Pappy Van Winkle 23 Year Barrel

review_blob: Draft @ GLBC CLE airport. Pours a deep golden to amber in color with minimal head, but nice lacing. Aroma of citrus, tropical fruit and malt. Medium body with appropriate carbonation. Taste is nice balance of malty sweetness, hop bitterness and a subtle citrus flavor. This is a very drinkable DIPA, with the alcohol well hidden.

Bottle poured into tulip. Pours a dark brown to black with minimal tan head. Aroma of apple, caramel, malt, and brandy. Medium to full body with a creamy mouth feel. Taste is apple, roasted malt, oak, Brandy, caramel and subtle chocolate, and vanilla. Alcohol definitely present, but not overwhelming. This a really sold sipper and probably Prairie's best offering to date.

Draft @ Mikkellar Bar SF on 2/5/14. Pours slightly hazy and golden in color with limited head and some lacing. Aroma is guava, grapefruit, mango with some malty sweetness. Medium bodied with some particulate. Palate is citrus and tropical fruits with a nicely balanced firm piney hop bitterness and some malty sweetness shining through. This is quite a nice IPA.

Draft @ City Beer Store on 2/3/15. Pours a slightly hazed golden color with 1 finger of white head and nice lacing. Aroma is pineapple, mango, citrus and some floral and dank elements from the hops. Medium bodied beer with nice carbonation. The flavor is solid with tropical and citrus fruits, a touch of malty sweetness and a floral, piney finish. A really nice DIPA.
beer_name: Altamont Beer Works / Knee Deep Hella Deep

review_blob: Draft @ City Beer Store on 2/3/15. Pours black as night with minimal brown head and some lacing. Aroma is bourbon, molasses, vanilla, chocolate, coffee, roasted malt, and dark fruit. Full bodied beer, but smooth as velvet. Palate is a luscious blend of molasses, bourbon, roasted malt, with hints of vanilla, chocolate, coffee and dark fruits. This beer should be enjoyed often, but slowly and in small quantities. The alcohol content is fairly hight, but well hidden in the flavor palate.
UPDATED: FEB 6, 2015

Poured from bottle into teku. Pours hazy and pale yellow in color with minimal bubbly head and minimal lacing. Aroma is mostly saison yeast with a citrusy lemon-lime overtone. Mouth feel is medium bodied and nicely carbonated. Palate is lemon, lime, and peppercornsour throughout and finishes dry. A nice saisoneasy drinker.
UPDATED: JUN 18, 2015
UPDATED: FEB 5, 2015
UPDATED: FEB 5, 2015
beer_name: Cellarmaker The Vastness of Space - Bourbon

review_blob: Draft @ Gourmet Haus Staudt on 1/29/15. Pours a deep red, brown in color with 1 finger of head and nice lacing. Aroma is strongly hop-driven dank and resinous with notes of pineapple and citrus and some subtle malty sweetness. Medium body. Palate is dank, floral and robust hop bitterness with some sweetness from the malt backbone. A nicely balanced beer.

On tap @ Gourmet Haus Staudt. Pours burgundy brown in color with minimal head. Aroma is maple, caramel, malt, and bourbon. Light to medium body, like a porter. Flavor is nicely balanced maple, brown sugar, bourbon, oak, and subtle pecan. This is really nicely balance beer and it solidly represents its name. The high alcohol content is well hidden. I could drink a few more of these easily.
beer_name: High Water Sugaree Maple Bourbon Pecan Pie

review_blob: 22 oz bottle poured into a snifter. Pours black with 1 finger of tan head. Aroma is roasted malt, chocolate, bourbon, vanilla, and oak. Medium body with a nice velvety texture. Flavor is a slightly sweeter version of the base beer with predominantly roasted malt, caramel, chocolate, coffee with subtle whiskey and oak.
beer_name: FiftyFifty Imperial Eclipse Stout - Mellow Corn Barrel

review_blob: 22 oz. bottle poured into pint glass. Pours copper in color with 1 finger of head and nice lacing. Aromas of grapefruit, citrus, pine, and malt. Medium body. Palate is balanced citrus, resinous bitterness and malt. A really nice IPAprobably the best in the Speakeasy Limited series.

12 oz. poured into a snifter. Pours a dark brown-black with 1 finger of tan head and nice lacing. Aroma is espresso, roasted malt, smoke, and lactose. Mouthfeel is medium bodied with a velvety texture. Palate is strongly coffee and roasted malt with a lingering bitterness. Very drinkable coffee milk stout.

Draft @ The Office on 1/23/15. Pours amber in color with minimal head. Aroma is strongly caramel, malt with some floral, citrus, and pineapple. Mouthfeel is medium to thin. Flavor is floral, citrus, grapefruit peel, malty, carmel with a lingering heavy bitterness. Not a particularly balanced offering, nor did I get the dankness that I would expect from the name "ganja juice."

Draft of EB 2/14/15 @ The Office on 1/23/15. Pours straw yellow with 1 finger of white head with good retention and lacing. Aroma is strongly citrus with subtle tropical fruits. Mouthfeel is medium bodied and a bit sticky. Palate is robustly citrus and resinous hops balanced nicely against the malt backbone and alcohol. Nicely balanced DIPA. Probably the best Enjoy By since the 4/20/14.

Draft @ Mikkeller Bar SF on 1/19/15. Pours a red, brown color with minimal head. Aroma is acidic, red grapes, malt, and brett. Medium to thin bodied. Taste is vinegar-like acidity with tones of cherry, grape and funk with a bitter finish. Decent flanders red.

Draft @ Mikkeller Bar SF on 1/19/15. Pours red in color with a slight pink head. Aroma of tart cherries, slight citrus and funk. Mouthfeel is acidic, medium bodied, well carbonated. Taste is tart cherry, citrus. Solid sour with good cherry flavor.

Draft @ Mikkeller Bar SF on 1/19/15. Pours a dark amber color with 1 finger of white head and good lacing. Aroma is dank pine, citrus and tropical fruits. Mouthfeel is medium bodied with resinous stickiness. Taste is solid combination of resinous hop bitterness with grapefruit and slight mango/peach flavors. This is a solid IPA.

Bottle @ City Beer Store on 1/19/15. Pours a clear dark red, brown color with tan head and lacing. Aroma is strongly bourbon and oak with some vanilla and dark fruit. Mouthfeel is full bodied with light to medium carbonation. Flavor is heavy bourbon and oak, brown sugar and caramel malt with some dark fruits. Overall a nice bourbon, oak-aged beer, but these flavors dominate the base beer (which is excellent).
beer_name: AleSmith Wee Heavy Scotch Ale - Barrel Aged

review_blob: Draft @ City Beer Store on 1/19/15. Pours a dark brown/burgundy with minimal tan head. Aroma of malty, raisin sweetness with some banana, cola nut and spice. Mouthfeel is medium bodied and creamy. Palate of dark fruit, malty sweet, cola and spice. Well balanced dark belgian with great aroma and flavor.
UPDATED: JAN 27, 2015
beer_name: Brewfist / Prairie Artisan Ales Spaghetti Western

review_blob: Draft @Mikkeller Bar SF on 1/19/15. Pours slightly hazy golden with limited white head and lacing. Aroma is malt with subdued citrus and tropical hop notes. Taste is mostly malt with minimal hop buttering and some citrus flavors. A bit thin in both aroma and flavor compared to other Cellarmaker PA offerings. I expected at least more aromatics.
UPDATED: JAN 27, 2015

Bottle poured into a snifter. Minimal head with some lacing. Aroma is mostly roasted malt, coffee and alcohol. Taste is predominantly coffee and roasted malt with a lingering alcohol burn. Decent barrel aged coffee stout, but not nearly best in style.
beer_name: Amager / Mikkeller Hr. Frederiksen Vsel Brunch BA

review_blob: Draft @ Ale Arsenal. Pours a dark amber to brown in color with virtually no head. Aroma is mostly bourbon and oak with some caramel and dark fruits. Palate of caramel, brown sugar, bourbon and oak with a hint of vanilla and rye. Fairly solid barrel-aged barley wine, although not nearly the best Ive tasted.
beer_name: Hangar 24 Barrel Roll No. 04: Hammerhead - Barrel Aged Barley Wine

review_blob: Draft 1/12/15 @ Harrys Hofbrau RWC. Pours dark brown with limited caramel colored head. Some lacing present. Aroma of bourbon, raisins, figs, and a bit of vanilla. Good mouthfeel, although a little thinner than the other BC offerings. Taste is dark fruits, bourbon, oak, vanilla, and possibly a hint of chocolate. Solid bourbon barrel aged barleywine.

Bottle on 1/9/15. Pours black in color with less than a finger of head. Good lacing. The aroma is roasted malt, bourbon, caramel, and chocolate, and vanilla. Good mouth feel. The taste is roasted malt and bourbon with some chocolate, vanilla, and caramel. Very nice bourbon barrel stout.

Bottle @ Ale Arsenal on 1/9/15. Pours black in color with one finger or less of head that dissipates quickly. Plenty of lacing. The aroma is bourbon, caramel, chocolate, and oak. Thinner mouth feel than many in the class, but similar to other Eclipse varietals. The taste is bourbon barrel and roasted malt upfront with some chocolate and caramel. Still a solid beer, but not nearly the best Eclipse varietal.
beer_name: FiftyFifty Imperial Eclipse Stout - High West Bourbon Barrel

review_blob: Draft @ Ale Arsenal on 1/9/15. Pours a yellow to amber color with 1 finger of head. Slight lacing. Aroma of pine, resin, citrus, and tropical fruits. Taste is quite dank with plenty of resinous goodness, but also nice balance with notes of citrus and tropical fruits with some malty character and alcohol present. Well balanced and not too boozy for a triple IPA. Solid and very drinkable.

Draft @ Harrys Hofbrau RWC on 1/9/15. Aroma of predominantly coffee with booze, hints of roasted malt and vanilla. Pleasant mouthfeel and tastes of coffee, roasted malt, bourbon, chocolate, and vanilla. Very solid for the stylecould drink several more of these.
beer_name: Goose Island Bourbon County Stout - Coffee

review_blob: UPDATED: JAN 12, 2015
beer_name: Hangar 24 Barrel Roll No. 03: Pugachevs Cobra - Barrel-Aged Imperial Stout

review_blob: 1/8/15 draft @ Ale Arsenal. Alpha Acid's first IPA offering is an aromatic hop bomb with plenty of crisp fruit and citrus notes from Nelson and Galaxy. There is plenty of welcome bittering from the Simcoe. Nice mouth feel and overall very drinkable.
